This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on the affect dimensions in portrayals of people. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to analyze the affect dimensions, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the limitations of the contextualized word embeddings, which is related to the field of machine learning and falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the biases in the training data, which is related to the field of cybersecurity and falls under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper also discusses the qualitative analysis of the results, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound).
